    {
      "id": "edge-class-authoring-overview",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Overview",
      "position": {
        "x": -260,
        "y": 120
      },
      "width": 820,
      "height": 300,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Edge Class Authoring Walkthrough\n\nThis is a manual, end-to-end test of the edge-class authoring loop.\n\n**Goal**\n- Start a new graph.\n- Define a new edge class (meaning + render).\n- Save it under the edge class library path.\n- Export it from the edge class library.\n- Import it from a fresh consumer graph.\n- Create 1–2 edges and assign the edge class.\n\n**Pass Criteria**\n- The new edge class appears in the legend/type selector.\n- The legend preview matches the on-canvas edge stroke (color, dash, arrow).\n- Selecting the edge type/class updates the on-canvas edge.\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "edge-class-authoring-step-1",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Step 1",
      "position": {
        "x": -260,
        "y": 460
      },
      "width": 400,
      "height": 260,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Step 1: Start A New Edge Class Graph\n\nAction:\n- Create a new graph (New File).\n- Add a **Declaration** node.\n- Set the declaration:\n  - Mode: `artifact`\n  - Artifact kind: `edge-class`\n  - Set graph id/name.\n\nResult:\n- [ ] PASS\n- [ ] FAIL\n\nNotes:"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "edge-class-authoring-step-2",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Step 2",
      "position": {
        "x": 160,
        "y": 460
      },
      "width": 400,
      "height": 260,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Step 2: Define The Edge Class (Nodes, Not JSON)\n\nReference contract:\n- `/library/documentation/contracts/edges/edge-class-contract.node`\n\n### A) Add `field` nodes (identity)\n1) Add a **Field** node.\n2) In Properties → Advanced → Relevant, set:\n   - `title`: `edgeClass.key`\n   - `fieldType`: `string`\n   - `value`: your stable key (example: `task.depends-on`)\n3) Repeat for:\n   - `edgeClass.label` (string)\n   - `edgeClass.meaning` (string)\n\n### B) Add `field` nodes (render defaults)\nCreate Field nodes:\n- `renderDefaults.stroke` (string hex like `#22c55e`)\n- `renderDefaults.width` (number)\n\nOptional:\n- `renderDefaults.dash` (json like `[22, 8]`)\n- `renderDefaults.routingHint` (string like `orthogonal`)\n\n### C) Add a port-consumable summary view (REQUIRED)\n- Add a `summary-view` node\n- Set `payload` = `node.web.summary`\n\n### D) Quick self-test (before Step 3)\n- Add 2 markdown nodes\n- Draw 1 edge\n- Verify the edge style matches the render defaults (color/width/dash)\n\nResult:\n- [ ] PASS\n- [ ] FAIL\n\nNotes:"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "edge-class-authoring-step-3",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Step 3",
      "position": {
        "x": 580,
        "y": 460
      },
      "width": 400,
      "height": 260,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Step 3: Save The Edge Class File\n\nAction:\n- Save the graph under the edge class library path:\n\n`/library/classes/edges/<your-edge-class-id>.edge-class.node`\n\nResult:\n- [ ] PASS\n- [ ] FAIL\n\nNotes:"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "edge-class-authoring-step-4",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Step 4",
      "position": {
        "x": -260,
        "y": 760
      },
      "width": 610,
      "height": 320,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Step 4: Export It From The Edge Class Library (REQUIRED)\n\nWhy:\n- Your edge class will **not** show up in consumer legends/type selectors until the library exports it.\n\nAction:\n1) Open the edge class library root graph:\n\n`/library/classes/edges/root.node#root`\n\n2) Add a **Bridge** node in the library graph pointing to your new edge class file.\n   - Target ref: `/library/classes/edges/<your-edge-class-id>.edge-class.node#root`\n\n3) Configure the Bridge:\n- Role: `export`\n- Resource kind: `edge-class`\n\n4) Update the library **export surface allowlist** (required):\n- Open the library **Declaration** node\n- Find `surfaces[]` where `kind = export`\n- Add your `edgeClass.key` to `exposes.edgeClasses.allowKeys`\n\nVerification:\n- From the library graph, the export surface should now include your key.\n\nResult:\n- [ ] PASS\n- [ ] FAIL\n\nNotes:"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "edge-class-authoring-step-5",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Step 5",
      "position": {
        "x": 370,
        "y": 760
      },
      "width": 610,
      "height": 320,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Step 5: Import And Test In A Fresh Consumer Graph\n\nAction:\n1) Create a new graph.\n2) Add a **Declaration** node.\n3) Add a **Bridge** node:\n- Role: `import`\n- Bridge Ref: `/library/classes/edges/root.node#root`\n- Grant: `Create` (implies consume)\n- Exposure: allow edge classes.\n\nThen:\n- Create 2 markdown nodes\n- Draw an edge\n- In edge properties, pick your new edge class\n\nIf your edge class is missing:\n- Re-check Step 4: export bridge exists AND the library export surface allowlist includes your `edgeClass.key`.\n\nResult:\n- [ ] PASS\n- [ ] FAIL\n\nNotes:"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "edge-class-authoring-expectations",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Expected Result",
      "position": {
        "x": -260,
        "y": 1120
      },
      "width": 1240,
      "height": 260,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Expected Result\n\n- The imported edge class appears in the legend/type selector.\n- The legend preview matches the on-canvas edge style (color, dash, arrowheads).\n- Changing the edge type/class updates the on-canvas edge.\n- The selection persists after save/reload.\n"
      }
    }
  ],
